18:58.312 --> 19:00.254
Talking about God's coming kingdom.

19:00.675 --> 19:05.842
Those who knew the word, that hurt Him as on the cross, didn't just hear words of despair.

19:05.902 --> 19:09.426
They heard the promise of the resurrection that was coming.

19:10.850 --> 19:20.871
The word was so much a part of Jesus that he used even his last breath to try to lead people to the life God intended them to lead.

19:21.653 --> 19:26.382
And so when he was standing over those elements and he was saying, this is my body.

19:26.723 --> 19:28.146
This is my blood.

19:29.858 --> 19:42.531
The cups that were there before them that they had shared in the ceremony were the cups of atonement, the cups of salvation, the cups of deliverance, and the cup that was never drank from, or the promise of the coming kingdom of Elijah.

19:45.154 --> 19:54.083
God has given us a precious word, a living word, a word for us to live by.

19:55.584 --> 19:57.426
And as we come to this communion,

19:57.986 --> 20:00.974
I want you to remember that God doesn't waste words.

20:04.643 --> 20:12.002
God's given us treasure and God's given us the opportunity for that word to become flesh in us.

20:13.245 --> 20:13.746
Let's pray.

